The alien's plan would have been perfect, however, they made one crucial mistake. The alien forgot to check if Matt Damon had been in the original movie, The Martian.

Had the alien checked that Matt Damon had starred in a movie about aliens, they would have had a much better chance at knowing what they were dealing with. Instead, they went in blind. They were completely and utterly mistaken in thinking that humans were all just dumb lumps of meat. They found out the hard way that humanity does have its perks. Fame leads to obsessions and stalker fans.

A group of twenty-somethings used drones to track the alien down. Kara, the queen of the Matt Damon Fan Club, had been following him with a drone for about seventeen years. She knew exactly where he was and how to find him. 
The group tracked the alien to a small town in Iowa.
 "Reeeeeeeee!" Squealed the alien upon the arrival of fifteen girls clad in crop tops and high-waisted jean shorts.

"Matt Damon!" Shouted a man that was restrained by chains. 

"Oh my god, the alien probed him!" One girl shouted.

"That's hot!" Another added. I'm going to have his babies!"



The girls surrounded the alien, and their faces were filled with terror.
 They couldn't believe what they were seeing. This was their idol, their hero. Matt Damon is a legend, and they had never witnessed him in such a vulnerable position.
"Let him go!"
 Kara shouted.
